<!-- This is a complete, self-contained HTML document for a news website's 404 error page. --><!-- It uses Tailwind CSS for modern, responsive styling. --><!DOCTYPE html><html lang="en"><head><meta charset="UTF-8"><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"><title>404 - Page Not Found</title><link href="/public/css/style.css" rel="stylesheet"></head><body class="flex items-center justify-center min-h-screen text-gray-800"><!-- Main container for the 404 content --><div class="max-w-xl mx-auto p-8 bg-white shadow-xl rounded-2xl text-center"><!-- Prominent 404 error code --><div class="mb-4"><h1 class="text-9xl font-extrabold text-red-500">404</h1></div><!-- Headline for the error page --><h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Page Not Found</h2><!-- Descriptive message for the user --><p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8 leading-relaxed"> Oops! The page you're looking for seems to have been lost in the news archives. It might have been removed, had its name changed, or is temporarily unavailable. </p><!-- Call to action to return to the homepage --><a href="/" class="inline-block bg-gray-100 text-white font-semibold py-3 px-8 rounded-full shadow-lg hover:bg-gray-300 transition duration-300 transform hover:scale-105"> Return to the Homepage </a><!-- Optional: A suggestion for "Latest News" --><p class="mt-8 text-sm text-gray-500"> You can also check out our <a href="/latest-news" class="text-blue-500 hover:underline">Latest News</a> section. </p></div></body></html>